\[0 \cdot 3 = 0\]
\[0 \cdot 1 = 0\]

Sum of these values:

\[19683 + 13122 + 0 + 1458 + 486 + 81 + 54 + 18 + 0 + 0 = 34802\]

Thus,

\[1202212200_3 = 34802_{10}\]

#### Perform the addition in base-10:

\[16317_{10} + 34802_{10} = 51119_{10}\]

#### Convert \(51119_{10}\) back to base-3:

To convert from base-10 to base-3, we repeatedly divide by 3 and record the remainders.

\[51119 \div 3 = 17039\] remainder \(2\)
\[17039 \div 3 = 5679\] remainder \(2\)
\[5679 \div 3 = 1893\] remainder \(0\)
\[1893 \div 3 = 631\] remainder \(0\)
\[631 \div 3 = 210\] remainder \(1\)
\[210 \div 3 = 70\] remainder \(0\)
\[70 \div 3 = 23\] remainder \(1\)
\[23 \div 3 = 7\] remainder \(2\)
\[7 \div 3 = 2\] remainder \(1\)
\[2 \div 3 = 0\] remainder \(2\)

Reading the remainders from bottom to top gives us:

\(51119_{10} = 2101010222_{3}\)

So, the original problem \(211112001_{3} + 1202212200_{3} = 2101010222_{3}\).

\[211112001_{3} + 1202212200_{3} = 211112001_{3} (16317_{10}) + 1202212200_{3} (34802_{10}) = 51119_{10} = 2101010222_{3}\]